The course deals with the theoretical principles related to therapeutic exercise and acquires during internships practical skills for the application of therapeutic exercises in the process of physiotherapy. Important topics covered in the course are the importance of therapeutic exercise, the components of the exercise, the effect of the exercise on organ systems, anatomical structures, mobilizing exercises based on joint mobility assessment, strength exercises based on muscle strength assessment, learning the correct movement pattern.
The course supports the development of various learning skills: the links between physiotherapeutic assessment and the choice of therapeutic exercises are created and analyzed, and the patient's therapeutic process is planned, carried out and documented.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to understand the importance of therapeutic exercise in the functions of the skeletal muscle system and other organ systems, and to acquire skills that enable to choose therapeutic exercise in the physiotherapy process based on the patient's functional capacity. The student can apply the theoretical knowledge and practical skills acquired in the course on the practice of the course.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course students: -understand the importance of therapeutic exercise in physiotherapy -can use different therapeutic exercise equipment's -are able to choose and supervise therapeutic exercises based on the patient's functional problem during the practice.
